      "response_text": "Great question! Nevada City and Grass Valley have wonderful dining options. Here are some top picks:\n\n**Nevada City:**\n- [[Tofanelli's Gold Country Bistro|tofanellis]] - Farm-to-table California cuisine on Broad Street\n- [[Cirino's at Main Street|cirinos]] - Italian comfort food, cozy atmosphere\n- [[MeZe Eatery|meze]] - Mediterranean flavors with local ingredients\n- [[Sergio's Caffe|sergios]] - Classic Italian, excellent pasta\n\n**Grass Valley:**\n- [[Watershed|watershed]] - Craft cocktails and seasonal small plates\n- [[Holbrooke Hotel|holbrooke]] - Historic hotel restaurant, Gold Rush ambiance\n- [[1849 Brewing Company|1849-brewing]] - Local brewery with pub fare\n- [[Wild Eye Pub|wild-eye]] - Gastropub with live music nights\n- [[Three Forks Bakery & Brewing Co.|three-forks]] - Artisan bread and craft beer\n- [[Friar Tuck's Restaurant|friar-tucks]] - Classic American, family-friendly\n\nFor a special evening, I'd recommend [[Lefty's Grill|leftys]] or [[Pianeta|pianeta]] in Grass Valley, or [[Moody's Bistro|moodys]] in Truckee if you're willing to drive.",
